TITLE: U.S. Navy sailor detained in Venezuela, officials say
SUMMARY: A U.S. State Department spokesperson said the department was tracking the service member’s detention and monitoring the situation

TITLE: New Maori Queen is anointed as her father, the King, is buried
SUMMARY: Representatives said Nga Wai Hono i te Po had been chosen by Maori elders to replace her father, King Tuheitia Pootatau Te Wherowhero VII, who died last week

TITLE: Pope urges fight against extremism and climate change at Southeast Asia's largest mosque
SUMMARY: Pope Francis and the grand imam of the mosque in Indonesia promoted interfaith dialogue in a highlight of the pontiff’s four-nation trip to Asia and Oceania

TITLE: Ex-Green Beret behind failed Venezuela raid released pending trial on weapons charges
SUMMARY: Jordan Goudreau was arrested in July after a four-year investigation into a raid that ended with several combatants killed by Venezuelan security forces

TITLE: Ugandan runner dies from burns inflicted by her partner after competing in Paris Olympics
SUMMARY: Rebecca Cheptegei, a distance runner, finished 44th in the marathon at the 2024 Paris Olympics

TITLE: Police shoot and kill armed man near Israeli Consulate and museum in Munich
SUMMARY: Israel’s Foreign Ministry said the consulate in Munich was closed when the shooting occurred and that no consulate staff had been affected by the incident

TITLE: 'It's unbearable': French woman testifies in case of husband, 50 men accused of raping her
SUMMARY: Dominique Pelicot and 50 other men are standing trial on charges of rape and face up to 20 years in prison.&nbsp

TITLE: $50 billion, a million jobs and a red carpet welcome: China woos Africa as U.S. struggles to keep up
SUMMARY: Chinese President Xi Jinping hosted dozens of leaders from the fast-growing continent, where the world’s two largest economies are competing for influence

TITLE: Harvey Weinstein indecent assault case ended by U.K. prosecutors
SUMMARY: Prosecutors concluded there was no realistic chance of securing a conviction

TITLE: North Korea's Kim touts his newest weapon: Exploding drones
SUMMARY: The U.S. and South Korea are holding joint military drills aimed at enhancing their ability to defend against growing North Korean nuclear threats
